20:16.424 --> 20:19.040
...there's gonna be a version of you,
10 years younger...

20:19.218 --> 20:21.459
...doing the same thing to you.

20:21.971 --> 20:23.552
And then who you gonna be?

20:24.014 --> 20:25.140
What?

20:25.307 --> 20:28.299
Yeah, that's right. You heard me.

20:30.479 --> 20:31.810
JASON:
Touchdown.

20:31.981 --> 20:34.768
Well, I guess the only way
to get a promotion in this town...

20:34.942 --> 20:36.443
...is to drink like a fish...

20:36.610 --> 20:38.987
...hallucinate farm animals,
and kill a black man.

20:39.155 --> 20:41.146
Hey, promotion. Ha, ha.

20:42.450 --> 20:43.940
Pig!

20:44.118 --> 20:45.904
ARLENE:
Ow! Shit.

20:46.078 --> 20:48.820
SAM: Here, let me help you.
-God, you wanna help me?

20:48.998 --> 20:50.488
How about doing yourjob, boss?

20:51.459 --> 20:55.873
Right now I'm a hostess, waitress,
bartender, busboy...

20:56.046 --> 20:58.173
...because everybody you hire
comes to work...

20:58.340 --> 21:00.592
...whenever they fucking feel like it
or ends up dead.

21:00.760 --> 21:01.795
[SOBBING]

21:01.969 --> 21:03.470
And I've got enough
on my plate without--

21:03.637 --> 21:06.174
I'll get someone else in here
soon enough, okay?

21:06.348 --> 21:08.930
You have got to start looking out
for your own, Sam.

21:09.101 --> 21:11.137
[BEER TRICKLING]

21:16.484 --> 21:19.351
-SooMe.
SOOKIE: In here.

21:23.324 --> 21:25.360
Wow.

21:25.534 --> 21:27.786
I guess my sister took to you.

21:27.953 --> 21:31.241
Debbie's getting initiated into
Coot's pack, and she's addicted to V.

21:31.415 --> 21:33.371
Shut the fucking door.

21:33.542 --> 21:35.248
Debbie's a bloodhead?
How'd you find out?

21:35.419 --> 21:37.501
I was poking around in Janice's brain.

21:37.671 --> 21:40.208
She didn't tell you
because she's trying to protect you.

21:40.382 --> 21:44.000
-Why didn't you let her?
-Because I know you care about Debbie.

21:44.178 --> 21:46.419
I figured you'd wanna know
if she were in danger.

21:46.597 --> 21:49.259
She's gonna let those fucking mongrels
brand her.

21:49.433 --> 21:52.391
-V's the only reason. It's gotta be.
-Of course it is.

21:52.561 --> 21:55.052
Maybe it's not too late
for you to get through to her.

21:55.231 --> 21:57.688
-Stop her from ruining her life.
-Fuck!

21:57.858 --> 21:59.314
[GLASS SHATTERS]
[ALCIDE SIGHS]

22:00.277 --> 22:01.813
That mean you're coming with me?

22:03.405 --> 22:05.566
I probably won't get in othenNise.

22:06.408 --> 22:07.784
Fine.

22:07.952 --> 22:10.068
We're gonna have to go in separate,
though.

22:10.246 --> 22:12.578
You might be able to fool some
with that getup.

22:12.748 --> 22:16.240
They're just gonna
beat the shit out of me, again.

22:18.170 --> 22:19.580
[DOOR OPENS THEN CLOSES]

22:19.755 --> 22:20.744
[SIGHS]

22:21.966 --> 22:25.550
How long did you work
for Sophie Anne?

22:25.719 --> 22:28.552
BILL: Thirty-five years.
-As?

22:28.722 --> 22:31.304
I was a procurer.

22:32.268 --> 22:33.929
Were you any good?

22:35.062 --> 22:36.427
I received no complaints.

22:36.605 --> 22:40.268
And then you started sampling
the local flavor in Bon Temps.

22:40.442 --> 22:42.728
No. I was on sabbatical.

22:43.571 --> 22:46.654
Well, now you're playing coy, William.

22:47.283 --> 22:49.490
So which is it you doubt,
my intentions...

22:51.453 --> 22:52.533
...or my power?

22:55.499 --> 22:58.457
Can you assure me that
you will be able to usurp her territory?

22:58.627 --> 23:02.336
Well, that depends on the quality
of your information, now, doesn't it?

23:02.506 --> 23:05.623
-No.
-I insist.

23:12.141 --> 23:15.429
"A woman is only a woman...

23:15.603 --> 23:17.935
...but a good cigar...

23:18.522 --> 23:19.853
...is a smoke."

23:20.024 --> 23:21.810
[RUSSELL CHUCKLES]

23:22.526 --> 23:24.812
Rudyard Kipling.

23:24.987 --> 23:28.275
No Shakespeare, but less impetuous.

23:28.449 --> 23:30.189
And he never stole spoons.

23:33.203 --> 23:36.695
Your Majesty, if I am going
to sign my own death warrant...

23:36.874 --> 23:38.535
...I will need something in return.

23:43.672 --> 23:46.004
When I have fulfilled my duties...

23:46.467 --> 23:48.753
...I want Lorena gone.

23:48.928 --> 23:50.008
Gone?

23:50.638 --> 23:52.094
Yes.

23:52.765 --> 23:55.632
It is a punishable offense
to kill another vampire.

23:55.809 --> 23:57.515
Not if no one reports it.

23:58.145 --> 24:00.227
RUSSELL:
Hmm.

24:09.198 --> 24:13.783
Eric Northman,
the queen's sheriff of Area 5...

24:13.953 --> 24:16.615
...has been selling vampire blood...

24:16.789 --> 24:19.576
...and I believe it is at her behest.

24:21.210 --> 24:23.917
If the Magister finds out,
he'll put her on trial.

24:24.088 --> 24:26.750
He's been itching for another inquisition
for centuries.

24:27.549 --> 24:31.883
-Why on earth would she be so stupid?
-The Great Revelation.

24:32.054 --> 24:35.638
She's close to losing her fortune
now that we're being taxed by the IRS.

24:35.808 --> 24:37.890
RUSSELL:
Hmm.

24:40.062 --> 24:42.769
Tug on the purse strings,
you'll find a lady's heart.

24:50.864 --> 24:52.400
That's very nice, Bill.

24:53.742 --> 24:55.733
Very nice.

24:58.038 --> 25:00.529
I feel like celebrating.

25:14.888 --> 25:16.799
[DOOR OPENS THEN CLOSES]

25:26.191 --> 25:27.442
Missed you.

25:39.872 --> 25:41.703
You miss me?

25:50.090 --> 25:51.671
Did you miss me?

26:00.893 --> 26:03.600
I can't stop thinking about you.

26:04.480 --> 26:06.345
Something about you is just so....

26:07.274 --> 26:09.139
What's the word?

26:09.318 --> 26:10.398
[GRUNTS]

26:10.569 --> 26:12.480
Motherfucker.

26:12.988 --> 26:14.979
Magical.

26:22.372 --> 26:25.580
We have so much ahead of us.

26:32.508 --> 26:35.625
When people come in, first thing,
count how many of them there are.

26:35.803 --> 26:38.169
More than two always gets a table,
never the bar.

26:38.347 --> 26:39.757
So say there's three.

26:40.140 --> 26:43.849
Pull out one, two, three menus
and walk them to their table.

26:44.019 --> 26:46.055
Well, what about the waitressing part?

26:46.230 --> 26:48.516
You gotta be 18 to serve alcohol
in Louisiana.

26:48.690 --> 26:51.853
That is so not fair.
I'm never gonna be 18.

26:52.027 --> 26:55.394
And I used to be the best server
at our church pancake night.

26:55.572 --> 26:57.187
Think you can handle it?

26:57.366 --> 26:59.231
I'm a vampire, not a fucking idiot.

26:59.660 --> 27:01.867
Uh, hi, welcome to Merlotte's.

27:02.037 --> 27:05.370
Table 5's available
if you'll just follow me right this way.

27:08.752 --> 27:11.084
A hostess ain't gonna help me
with my workload.

27:11.255 --> 27:13.712
And she sure as heck
ain't helping herself to my tips.

27:13.882 --> 27:17.124
Calm down. I put an ad in the Pennysaver
for another waitress.

27:17.302 --> 27:19.588
No one said anything
about Jessica getting tips.

27:19.763 --> 27:21.799
People love giving redheads tips.

27:23.058 --> 27:25.925
And I've always been the only redhead
at Merlotte's, Sam.

27:26.103 --> 27:27.764
You know that.

27:28.689 --> 27:30.930
Sorry, Sam.

27:31.108 --> 27:33.895
Ah, I get a little emotional when I'm--

27:34.570 --> 27:38.939
When I see people
taking advantage of you.

27:39.408 --> 27:44.744
-What are you talking about?
-Well, you let in every stray, Sam.

27:44.913 --> 27:49.077
I mean, first that old dog,
and then your folks, and now Jessica.

27:49.251 --> 27:52.243
I mean, it's your business,
it's not a charity.

27:52.421 --> 27:55.754
I can take care of myself. My folks
won't be coming around anymore.

27:55.924 --> 27:59.291
You sure they know that?
Because they're grilling in the parking lot.

28:04.391 --> 28:08.100
One thing's for sure, we'll never be
as bad of parents as they are.

28:08.270 --> 28:10.932
JESSICA: Well, your server
will be right with you, all right?

28:11.857 --> 28:13.973
-Oh, excuse me.
-Sorry.

28:14.151 --> 28:16.733
Jessica? Jessica Hamby?

28:16.904 --> 28:18.110
Um....

28:18.280 --> 28:21.864
-No, you've got me confused, I think.
-Jessica, it's Chip from Bible study.

28:25.370 --> 28:27.110
Hi. Oh, my God.

28:27.998 --> 28:32.287
I can't believe you're alive.
Your folks are gonna be so happy.

28:32.961 --> 28:35.794
-My God, it's a miracle.
-Yeah, I guess so.

28:35.964 --> 28:37.829
Oh, praise Jesus. Praise him.

28:41.803 --> 28:42.838
CALVIN:
You shitting me?

28:43.013 --> 28:45.129
My little brother
just got busted dealing dope.

28:45.599 --> 28:48.386
You won't find a better product.

28:49.311 --> 28:50.721
-You a cop?
-No, sir.

28:50.896 --> 28:53.012
I know your boy's a lean,
mean selling machine.

28:53.190 --> 28:54.896
I'm just here to up your game.

28:55.067 --> 28:59.231
Help you step up in the world,
clean some shit up.

28:59.404 --> 29:02.066
I'll go grab the Dirt Devil from Felton.

29:05.994 --> 29:08.736
-See if he's hungry too.
CRYSTAL: I ain't his mama.

29:09.665 --> 29:12.828
What you say? You feel me?

29:15.170 --> 29:20.665
Nothing this hot will cost you this little
and earn you so much.

29:21.677 --> 29:24.339
We're not getting in business
with people like you.

29:24.846 --> 29:26.837
People like me?

29:27.015 --> 29:29.552
-Look--
-No, you look, son.

29:29.726 --> 29:32.638
Polite's in short supply around here.
It's time you get your ass home.

29:32.813 --> 29:33.802
[CRASH]

29:33.981 --> 29:36.848
FELTON: Let's get these tires off.
-HeyI

29:37.025 --> 29:39.562
FELTON: Oh, ain't you pretty, princess?
LAFAYETTE: Hey!

29:41.154 --> 29:43.440
-Get the fuck up out my ride.
-How about no?

29:43.615 --> 29:45.526
-How about I whup your fucking ass?
-Faggot

29:45.701 --> 29:48.158
Unh. I told you
we ain't so polite around here.

29:48.328 --> 29:50.034
[LAFAYETTE GROANS]

30:06.263 --> 30:08.754
How'd you end up
in Bon Temps tonight?

30:08.932 --> 30:10.217
I was just on my way home...

30:10.392 --> 30:14.055
...back from picketing the baby-killer
factory up in Birmingham.

30:14.730 --> 30:16.891
-Stopped for a bite.
-No.

30:17.065 --> 30:18.726
You wanted to stop for a bite...

30:18.900 --> 30:22.518
...but you decided it was too late,
so you drove straight home.

30:23.697 --> 30:25.403
-It is late.
-Mm-hm.

30:27.576 --> 30:30.113
Then you got a little lost on the 165...

30:30.287 --> 30:33.905
...and that's why you got home
a little late and a little hungry.

30:34.291 --> 30:37.408
And you never even saw me.

30:38.503 --> 30:40.459
I hate being hungry before bed.

30:40.630 --> 30:42.621
[SIGHS AND CHUCKLES]

30:50.432 --> 30:51.467
FELTON:
Take that.

30:51.683 --> 30:53.674
[ALL CHUCKLING]

30:54.561 --> 30:56.552
[MAN CHOKING]

30:58.106 --> 31:00.483
Get your fucking hands off me,
dead man.

31:01.401 --> 31:03.983
-Take the deal.
-You'll have to kill me first.

31:04.154 --> 31:07.271
No, I think I'll kill
all your brother-cousins first.

31:07.866 --> 31:10.778
-How does that sound, Lafayette?
-Oh, that-- That sounds good.

31:11.161 --> 31:13.322
-Excellent.
-Unh. We'll sell.

31:14.206 --> 31:15.537
Just let me fucking go.

31:16.792 --> 31:18.328
[CALVIN GRUNTS]

31:18.502 --> 31:21.209
And that's called closing the deal.

31:22.506 --> 31:24.167
[WHISTLES]

31:24.341 --> 31:26.297
Let's go, RuPaul.

31:28.470 --> 31:31.086
LAFAYETTE:
Get the fuck up out of here.

31:35.102 --> 31:37.093
TARA: What do you want
with Sookie and Bill?

31:37.270 --> 31:38.851
FRANKLIN:
Nothing.

31:39.314 --> 31:43.023
My employer's interested in them.
Him, mostly.

31:43.193 --> 31:45.605
That where we're going?
To your employer?

31:45.779 --> 31:50.899
"Slappy's Snack Shack, five miles.
Persimmons and cherries."

31:51.076 --> 31:52.862
[LAUGHS]

31:53.036 --> 31:57.496
If there is one thing that I miss more
than sunshine, it is good fruit.

31:57.666 --> 31:58.826
Where are you taking me?

31:59.000 --> 32:01.252
Here I am
trying to make pleasant conversation...

32:01.420 --> 32:03.035
...and you wanna ruin my surprises.

32:03.213 --> 32:06.831
There ain't nothing pleasant
about being bitten and tied up.

32:07.008 --> 32:10.500
You're tough.
I could taste it in your blood.

32:12.389 --> 32:13.674
I'm not a bad guy, Tara.

32:13.849 --> 32:16.511
I just wanna make sure
that we have a chance.

32:17.936 --> 32:20.723
Untie my hands.
I'll give you whatever chance you want.

32:21.231 --> 32:24.064
Are you like this
with your other boyfriends?

32:24.234 --> 32:28.398
-This is kidnapping.
-This is opportunity.

32:30.115 --> 32:35.326
My job supports my financial needs.
My emotional ones....

32:38.248 --> 32:42.617
-|t's just there's so much I wanna tell you.
-Then tell me where we're going.

32:42.794 --> 32:44.876
I've been so lonely.

32:45.589 --> 32:47.705
But now you're mine...

32:48.717 --> 32:50.708
...all that's changed.

33:14.910 --> 33:18.118
I figured the sooner you left Bon Temps,
the happier you'd be.

33:19.414 --> 33:21.279
Unless you plan
on stealing from me more.

33:23.418 --> 33:25.784
You don't know shit about me.

33:28.632 --> 33:31.874
Well, I know you got a pretty raw deal
with your folks.

33:33.720 --> 33:36.336
I know you think I got off easy.

33:36.515 --> 33:39.348
Why'd you even look us up, anyway?

33:45.273 --> 33:48.231
Well, when I was your age...

33:49.402 --> 33:51.654
...I had no example.

33:54.616 --> 33:56.902
Everything I did--

33:57.953 --> 34:00.069
Shit that was worse than stealing,
by the way.

34:00.247 --> 34:01.612
--I did blind.

34:03.124 --> 34:04.159
And I survived...

34:04.626 --> 34:08.118
...but it caught up with me so bad,
sometimes I wished I hadn't.

34:08.296 --> 34:11.288
Guess I wanted to see
how different it could have been.

34:12.717 --> 34:13.968
And now that you have?

34:15.470 --> 34:18.633
I see that I can't get back what I lost.

34:19.307 --> 34:21.684
But you're still young...

34:22.477 --> 34:25.389
...and you don't have to make
the same mistakes.

34:26.064 --> 34:28.350
And you could stay with me.

34:29.150 --> 34:31.482
-I could set you up at the bar.
-You don't get it.

34:31.653 --> 34:34.395
My folks are fucked up,
but they can't get by without me.

34:34.573 --> 34:37.485
Now, I know it feels like that,
but they're not your problem.

34:37.659 --> 34:38.865
That's all they are.

34:39.035 --> 34:43.244
I ditch them tomorrow, they end up
in the gutter by the end of next week.

34:43.415 --> 34:44.996
You think I can live with that?

34:48.211 --> 34:51.703
I won't be free of these people
until the day they die.

34:55.468 --> 34:57.800
Well, I have to say
I'm a little disappointed.

34:57.971 --> 35:03.682
I pegged you as a professional, but clearly,
you lack the necessary artistry.

35:04.936 --> 35:08.053
Bossman, have you seen this face?

35:08.231 --> 35:09.732
It ain't nothing but art.

35:09.899 --> 35:12.811
Well, you walk into every situation
all flash and fire.

35:12.986 --> 35:15.352
You expect them to adapt to you.

35:15.530 --> 35:18.488
That's not salesmanship, it's ego.

35:18.700 --> 35:21.112
[PHONE RINGING]

35:24.456 --> 35:26.196
-What?
PAM: We 're being raided.

35:27.459 --> 35:29.996
ERIC [IN SWEDISH]:
80? Call the American Vampire League...

35:30.170 --> 35:33.378
...they'll get their lawyers on it. I'm busy.

35:33.548 --> 35:36.290
PAM [IN SWEDISH]:
It's not the police...

35:36.593 --> 35:38.083
...the Magister.

35:38.261 --> 35:39.376
I'm coming there now.

35:39.554 --> 35:41.510
Don't be stupid.
Leave while you still can.

35:41.681 --> 35:43.387
They're looking for the V, Eric.

35:43.558 --> 35:44.673
The Queen set you up.

35:44.851 --> 35:45.840
[DOOR OPENS]

35:46.019 --> 35:50.103
MAGISTER:
Come out, come out, wherever you are.

35:50.273 --> 35:52.935
[IN ENGLISH]
Magister. What a pleasant surprise.

35:53.109 --> 35:55.942
Oh, there's nothing pleasant about this.

35:56.112 --> 35:59.400
This is blasphemy.

36:00.408 --> 36:01.568
Take her.

36:03.995 --> 36:05.405
LAFAYETTE:
I know I ain't got no fangs...

36:05.580 --> 36:08.913
...and I know I can't talk whatever
language that is you talk in...

36:09.084 --> 36:12.417
...but I can move your shit.

36:16.466 --> 36:17.876
Oh, hell.

36:18.051 --> 36:21.168
How am I supposed to deal
with this fucked-up-ness?

36:23.807 --> 36:26.924
Hey, Andy. I wanna be a cop. A real one.

36:27.102 --> 36:31.596
-That's good, Stackhouse.
-Yeah. I've been old Jason long enough.

36:31.773 --> 36:35.265
Well, apply yourself like I told you,
someday you might make a good one.

36:39.989 --> 36:42.480
JASON:
No, I don't think you're hearing me.

36:42.659 --> 36:44.775
You see,
I'm not doing them fake ride-alongs...

36:44.953 --> 36:47.319
...and filling out forms.

36:47.497 --> 36:50.034
I'm thinking there's gotta be
an easier way.

36:50.208 --> 36:52.870
Ah, you've been thinking that way
your whole life, Stackhouse.

36:53.044 --> 36:54.955
Where's it gotten you?

36:56.464 --> 36:59.456
You're gonna make me a cop,
and you're gonna make me one now.

36:59.634 --> 37:03.297
Jason, even if I wanted to, I couldn't.
There's rules.

37:03.471 --> 37:08.215
There any rules about taking
TV interviews and promotions...

37:08.393 --> 37:10.429
...for not shooting a killer dead...

37:10.603 --> 37:12.935
...when I'm the one
who's gotta live with doing it?

37:13.106 --> 37:14.141
Any rules about that?

37:14.315 --> 37:16.601
I push this,
it'll blow up for the both of us.

37:16.776 --> 37:19.233
You know, I read something
in all that cop homework...

37:19.404 --> 37:24.194
...about when you make up stories
about murderers and crimes.

37:24.367 --> 37:26.198
What do they call that again?

37:26.995 --> 37:32.285
-Falsifying evidence.
-Yeah, falsifying evidence.

37:33.042 --> 37:35.203
Last few days...

37:35.378 --> 37:39.997
...shooting a known killer,
tackling a drug dealer in Hotshot...

37:40.175 --> 37:41.790
[SIGHS]

37:41.968 --> 37:47.213
I'm already the best cop you got,
Sheriff Andy Bellefleur.

37:52.312 --> 37:53.347
[DOOR OPENS THEN CLOSES]

37:53.521 --> 37:55.512
AW, Shit.

37:56.941 --> 38:00.229
MELINDA: Uh-huh.
These dogs plumping up real good.

38:02.113 --> 38:03.614
There you are.

38:04.032 --> 38:07.149
Boy, I'll whup you.

38:12.791 --> 38:14.873
Now, here's what's gonna happen.

38:16.461 --> 38:21.706
I'm gonna give you a place to stay
for now till you get back on your feet.

38:21.883 --> 38:24.090
No more stealing...

38:24.677 --> 38:26.713
...no more drinking...

38:26.888 --> 38:28.048
...or the deal's off.

38:28.223 --> 38:30.339
I think we can manage that.

38:32.560 --> 38:34.551
Don't see why not.

38:34.729 --> 38:36.435
Tommy?

38:36.606 --> 38:39.393
Think you can fly straight from now on?

38:40.401 --> 38:41.937
Supposed to be a joke.

38:46.282 --> 38:47.897
Maybe I can.

38:53.373 --> 38:57.787
-No. No, no, no, not you.
-Russell's expecting me.

38:57.961 --> 39:00.247
He's out. He'll be a while.

39:00.672 --> 39:02.003
We'll wait.

39:04.676 --> 39:06.712
TALBOT:
Is this for me?

39:10.139 --> 39:11.970
It's skinny.

39:23.778 --> 39:25.769
[CHATTERING]

39:30.201 --> 39:32.487
ALCIDE:
Itâ€™s a private party. Hollis ain't here.

39:33.746 --> 39:34.872
We 're on our own.

39:35.039 --> 39:36.620
MAN 1: Yeah.
